1) first way of debuggin is to have unit testing and integration testing in place in order to test our chef code 
    locally on workstation with contacting the chef server
2) Integration testing is done with the tool called Test kitchin and unit testing is done using what is called 
    rspec testing.
3) We can take a help of the below chef doc page in order to understand the chef code style in ruby
    https://docs.chef.io/ruby/
4) We can also check the syntax of the recipe file using the below command of ruby
    ruby -c my_cookbook_file.rb 
    This is going to compile the recipe and see if it works or not
5) We could use the below URL in order to have a look at the debug related stuff for the broker chef-client
    run
    https://docs.chef.io/debug/
